    • Model Creation¶

    In [8]:
    def create_model():
    model = Sequential([
        Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(3, 3), padding='same', activation='relu', input_shape=(IMG_WIDTH, IMG_HEIGHT, 3)),
        MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)),
        Conv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=(3, 3), padding='same', activation='relu'),
        MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)),
        Conv2D(filters=128, kernel_size=(3, 3), padding='same', activation='relu'),
        MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)),
        Flatten(),
        Dropout(rate=0.2),
        Dense(units=128, activation='relu'),
        Dropout(rate=0.2),
        Dense(units=5, activation='softmax')
    ])
      
    return model
    In [9]:
    cnn_model = create_model()
    In [10]:
    cnn_model.summary()
optimizer = Adam(learning_rate=0.002)

    labels = ["colon_aca","colon_n","lung_aca", "lung_n", "lung_scc", ]  #list of predicted class labels (labels)
test_dataset = 'testset/'  #directory containing test data (test_dataset)

test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1.0/255)

test_generator = test_datagen.flow_from_directory(test_dataset,
                                                 shuffle=False,
                                                 batch_size=1,  # Set batch size to 1 to iterate through all images
                                                 target_size=(IMG_WIDTH, IMG_HEIGHT),
                                                 class_mode='categorical')

predictions = cnn_model.predict(test_generator)

# Create a list of indices for shuffling
num_samples = len(test_generator)
shuffled_indices = list(range(num_samples))
random.shuffle(shuffled_indices)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=5, figsize=(12, 10))
idx = 0

for i in range(2):
    for j in range(5):
        if idx < num_samples:  # Check if we've displayed all samples
            # Get the index based on the shuffle order
            shuffled_idx = shuffled_indices[idx]
            predicted_label = labels[np.argmax(predictions[shuffled_idx])]
            
            # Get the name of the image file
            image_filename = test_generator.filenames[shuffled_idx]
            
            title = f"Predicted: {predicted_label}\nFile: {image_filename}"
            
            ax[i, j].set_title(title, fontsize=10, color='black')
            
            img = test_generator[shuffled_idx][0][0]
            ax[i, j].imshow(img)
            ax[i, j].axis("off")
        
        else:
            break
        idx += 1

plt.tight_layout()
plt.suptitle("Test Dataset Predictions", fontsize=20)
plt.show()

    In [21]:
    cf_mtx = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)

group_counts = ["{0:0.0f}".format(value) for value in cf_mtx.flatten()]
group_percentages = ["{0:.2%}".format(value) for value in cf_mtx.flatten()/np.sum(cf_mtx)]
box_labels = [f"{v1}\n({v2})" for v1, v2 in zip(group_counts, group_percentages)]
box_labels = np.asarray(box_labels).reshape(5, 5)

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 10))
sns.heatmap(cf_mtx, xticklabels=labels, yticklabels=labels,
           cmap="YlGnBu", fmt="", annot=box_labels)
plt.xlabel('Predicted Classes')
plt.ylabel('True Classes')
plt.show()
